    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "In this prophetic tradition narrated through two alternative chains reaching companions Ibn Abbas and Anas ibn Malik, the Prophet Muhammad (s) declares that showing enmity toward Imam Ali (AS) is equivalent to waging war against God, and harboring doubt about Ali constitutes disbelief. This was delivered in the context of establishing Ali's divinely-ordained authority, where the early Muslim audience understood nasb (enmity) as the active opposition to Ali's position that the Prophet had repeatedly affirmed.",
        "key_terms": {
          "ناصب": "Nasaba — to show enmity, hostility; a Nasibi is one who actively opposes Ali and the Ahlulbayt",
          "حارب": "Haraba — to wage war, to be at war with; here metaphorical for opposing the divine will",
          "كافر": "Kafir — disbeliever, one who rejects the truth; here indicating the severity of doubting Ali's station"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did the Prophet Muhammad say about showing enmity toward Imam Ali?"
      },
